{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"[operator-attested] evidence — mcp-publisher pin correctness. Ran `make verify-mcp-pin` in-session (independently, not just the implementer): it downloads the exact pinned URL and asserts byte-for-byte digest equality. Output:\n  pinned URL    = https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry/releases/download/v1.8.0/mcp-publisher_linux_amd64.tar.gz\n  pinned SHA256 = 1370446bbe74d562608e8005a6ccce02d146a661fbd78674e11cc70b9618d6cf\n  downloaded    = 1370446bbe74d562608e8005a6ccce02d146a661fbd78674e11cc70b9618d6cf (7337300 bytes)\n  RESULT: OK — the pinned digest matches the live download.\nThe digest also matches upstream registry_1.8.0_checksums.txt (confirmed by the implementer). So the embedded SHA-256 is correct for the pinned URL (not just that the sha256sum -c mechanism works).\n\nHeld-out TDD validation: full oracle 16 passed / 3 skipped locally (the sha256sum -c tests skip off-GNU; run in CI on ubuntu). Real zizmor: 'No findings (1 suppressed = the annotated excessive-permissions on mcp_registry)'; teeth-verified — unpinning one action makes zizmor report error[unpinned-uses] (high) AND the structural test fail. Real actionlint: clean. make lint + typecheck clean."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784141148003904001,"uuid":"f01bed5c-e730-4cad-9da8-96da5e6f6e01"}